<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="755" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/82</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Austrian Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Prochnik</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-19"><hi rend="italic">March 19,
                                1928</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 59/R</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to state that I am
                            authorized to assure you that the Austrian Government intends to make a
                            settlement of the relief debt at the earliest practicable date, and that
                                <pb facs="1025" n="897" xml:id="pg_897"/> it is prepared to make
                            with the United States a settlement on a basis no less favorable to the
                            United States than made with the other relief creditor governments, or
                            any of them.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar Prochnik</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>